President Muhammadu Buhari has joined people and government of Tunisia in mourning President Beji Caid Essebsi, 92. President Buhari, in a statement by his media aide ,Garba Shehu, noted that the passing of Essebsi, who is the first democratically elected leader of the North African country, will create a vacuum in the polity. He urged citizens to find encouragement and solace in the legacies of President Essebsi. President Buhari said: “His death marks the end of an era in the politics of Tunisia. The country has lost a father figure. “The Nigerian government and people extend heartfelt condolences to his family, and the government and people of Tunisia.”